{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"d1b1c8eedde3aa71b59b79f4d58cfdf06e38d662"},"timestamp":1456838920,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxMzc1NzQ0OTM=","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/Cpanel-JSON-XS/issues/59","origin":"github"},"title":"/ is accepted on decode and isn't escaped as \\/ when encoding","message":"JSON::XS and Cpanel::JSON::XS both accepts `{\"key\":\"1 / 5\"}` when decoding and also outputs this when encoding { key =\u003e \"1 / 5\" }.\n\nSee http://json.org for the definition of string which lists / ('solidus') as only valid when escaped.\n\nJSON::Tiny is correct in that regard.","files":null}]}